      <div class="ltx_para" id="S2.p6">
       <p class="ltx_p" id="S2.p6.1">
        As shown in Fig.
        <a class="ltx_ref" href="#S2.F3" title="Figure 3 ‚Ä£ II Observable bifurcations ‚Ä£ Multi-Stream Inflation: Bifurcations and Recombinations in the Multiverse">
         <span class="ltx_text ltx_ref_tag">
          3
         </span>
        </a>
        , the universe is broken into patches during multi-stream inflation. There are wall-like boundaries between these patches. During inflation, these boundaries are initially domain walls. However, after the recombination of the trajectories, the tensions of these domain walls vanish. We call these objects domain fences. As is well known, domain wall causes disasters in cosmology because of its tension. However, without tension, domain fence does not necessarily cause such disasters. It is interesting to investigate whether there are observational sequences of these domain fences.
       </p>
      </div>
      <div class="ltx_para" id="S2.p7">
